    "body": "### Problem\n\nI set `vim.opt.mouse = \"n\"` in my `init.lua`, in vim, if `mouse` is set to `'n'`, user can drag mouse and the cursor just go with mouse in normal mode, never entering visual mode. However, if I set it in nvim, once I drag the mouse in normal mode, or double clicking mouse drop me in visual mode, and since `\"v\"` is not set in `mouse`, dragging fallback to terminal behavior.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua init.lua\nvim.opt.mouse = \"n\"\n```\n\nthen drag text in normal mode\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBehave like vim, cursor just go with mouse.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0 commit g2c960e8f04\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.1236\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole 24.12.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nArch Linux CN repo",
